# AGENT TOOLSET (`hermes-web-chat`)

## Expose to web users

`web_search`, `web_extract`, `web_file_*`, `web_skill_*`, `memory`, `todo`, `session_search`, `vision_analyze`, `image_generate`, `web_knowledge_search` (when implemented).

## NEVER expose

`terminal`, `process`, `code_execution`, `browser_*`, `delegate_task`, upstream `skill_manage`, upstream `read_file`/`write_file`/`patch`/`search_files`.

Use `web_file_*` wrappers instead.

## Adding a new sandboxed tool

1. Implement handler in `gateway/web/tools/` — call upstream public function after `confine_path`.
2. Register schema in same file's `_REGISTRATIONS`.
3. Import side-effect in `gateway/web/tools/__init__.py`.
4. Add tool name to `hermes-web-chat` in `toolsets.py`.
5. **Tests first** in `tests/gateway/test_web_sandboxed_*.py`.

## Skill isolation note

Do not expose upstream `skill_manage` — `SKILLS_DIR` is frozen at import time. Use `web_skill_*` only.
